"reviewcomment":"We arrived for our dinner reservation at 7:30pm but found the door was locked.  A local friendly Italian woman made them open it for us and they gave us white wine on the house. We were seated at around 8pm and then ordered.<br><br>Food ordered included mixed seafood appetizer, lobster spaghetti, squid Ink tagliatelle with cuttlefish, grilled eggplant and zucchini.<br><br>Antipast misto included baccala, octopus, cuttlefish, sardines, squid innards, mini shrimps, scallops and polenta.  Everything was tender, especially the inside of the squid.  <br><br>The squid ink pasta had the most tender cuttlefish I have eaten along with homemade tagliatelle with black squid ink. The portions were huge for the pasta. <br><br>This is another one of my favorite restaurants during my visit to Italy. Will definitely return.<br><br>They are moving to a larger location soon.",
