"ogimage":"http://s3-media2.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/MiN_ZbLrrLZG5EtNynQdDQ/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"Definitely my favourite spot in all of Venice! I discovered Osteria da Baco several years ago on a cold, winter&#39;s day. As I was loafing around outside of the shops my wife and friends were exploring, I noticed a number of gonoliers disappear into Osteria da Baco for a quick coffee or a glass of wine. Well, if it&#39;s good enough for gondoliers, it&#39;s good enough for me. The atmosphere was brilliant and the coffee and wine were extremely reasonable. Franco, the owner, and his family were so friendly and made me most welcome. Since then, I have been back to Venice many, many times, summer and winter, often with friends. My last visit was October 2010. I always spend some time at Osteria da Baco, enjoying a carafe of local wine and tasing some of their stupendous, freshly made sandwiches and foccacia. A great, fresh lunch with a glass of wine in Venice for around 6 Euro! If you are anywhere near San Zaccharia, make the effort to walk up Calle della Rasse and visit this place. You will not be disappointed.<br><br> Alan Couser, Northern Ireland",
