"rating":"4.5",
"reviewcomment":"I flew 5,450 miles to eat a pizza. Now that&#39;s decadence.<br><br>Enter Rosa Rossa...<br><br>Nestled in the myriad of labyrinth-like streets of Venice lies a gem that shines bright-even during a snow storm; even during acqua alta. If the commute from San Francisco wasn&#39;t so extensive you would see me at the chefs in the corner six nights a week. <br><br>I trekked through a foot of snow last time in Venice to make sure that I could have my chewy crispy pizza-which was absolute perfection-that followed an exquisitely fresh mozzarella di bufala caprese antipasto. <br><br>I trust the owner&#39;s (and his wife&#39;s) taste implicitly and enjoy it when he brings the wine he prefers for what I&#39;m eating that evening to the table without me looking at the wine list. <br><br>Each time I visit I wonder if I&#39;ve conjured such culinary perfection in my dreams (for I truly believe that the beauty of simplistic food where the emphasis is on taste and quality, not on fancy combinations like many California/Italian fusion cuisine) and then suddenly I take the deeply anticipated bite. Although I float in the clouds while enjoying the dream the staff has truly created there (from the music, to the ambience, to the staff in general) I know I am firmly tethered to the ground so that I can come back and enjoy Rosa Rossa again tomorrow evening.",
