"reviewcomment":"This is really a great place - you couldn&#39;t ask for a better location - on the Dorsoduro quayside close to Zattere vaporetto stop, but not so close you can hear the boats.<br><br> Visually it&#39;s everything a waterside restaurant should be at night - white clothed tables, smart waiters, candlelight throughout and, as it&#39;s Italy chic, well turned out diners.<br><br> It&#39;s not so cheap but far from outrageous - two starters (seafood rissotto), two main courses (one seabass, one wild boar), 3 glasses of excellent wine, 2 coffees, mineral water, EUR85 inc service.<br><br> All of this wouldn&#39;t amount to 5 stars if the wild boar hadn&#39;t been something genuinely exceptional. Intensely seasoned wrapped in panchetta and cooked until the centre had only just stopped bleeding but was still translucent - brave and difficult to get right but perfect for wild boar.<br><br> On the downside a reservation is pretty much essential . . . it doesn&#39;t matter how beautiful or well conncected you are - no reservation - join the queue for a table!",
