"reviewcomment":"Find this place by the palazzo fortuny. Modern, sleek atmosphere, dark lighting, exposed brick and American Celebrity clothing adorns the walls, haha.<br><br>That said, the food is great. Price is a little steep, sure, but walking in rain and wind in the middle of March will make one want to take shelter and comfort instead of saving two dollars on a glass of wine. <br><br>We dined with 4 total. Friendly server, speaking some english. Very busy place though, gets crowded for dinner.<br><br>Calzones are HUGE- downside... once you bite into the calzone, the air deflates the hope of a dish that was stuffed 4 inches high with fillings. Still very well baked, flaky crust. My girlfriend had an egg/ham/rocket/mozzarella one, and the egg was a nice flavor touch to the salty ham. <br><br>Pizzas were flavorful, large, and heavily topped with yummy creations, including a pizza that they forewarn you is extra spicy, which to me wasn&#39;t so bad. <br><br>Had the panna cotta with caramel for dessert, and that was wonderful... the caramel was more of a dulce de leche combination with the dish, but great.<br><br>Our friends had the berry crisp, which had an interesting and well-added crunch from ground up almonds, I believe, on the crust, which was amazing.<br><br>Worth finding amidst the mazes of Venice.",
