"reviewcomment":"Wow.<br><br> This Venetian restaurant has local and Tuscan specialities. Our hotel advised us to book a table as it&#39;s popular and has seating for only about 40.<br><br> The meal we had at Cucina da Mario (<a href='/redir?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.qype.co.uk%2Fplace%2F133809-Cucina-da-Mario-Venice&amp;s=96cabbac858f227fa0192329ed8b5a7ac0be6d1566da15adfec9dde116278b71' target='_blank' rel='nofollow'>qype.co.uk/place/133809-…</a>) was like your Italian grandmother might make for you. In contrast, the meal here was the stereotypical image I had of what eating in an Italian restaurant would be like: informal, great attention from waiters, five courses (plus dolci!) of incredibly fresh, simple, delicious food, and more wine than I could hope to choose from.<br><br> The meal was delicious and filling enough that I wrote it all down. I had the meat menu, my missus had the fish menu:<br><br> 1st (me; wife) - assorted meats; raw fish selection with pomegranate<br>2nd - bruschetta; flour polenta with shrimp<br>3rd - carrot, potato and cheese soup; fish soup<br>4th - pasta carbonara; spinach and mushroom sphagetti<br>5th - lamb with beans and potato; swordfish with soufflé<br>dolci - chocolate tart; chocolate tart<br><br> I don&#39;t recall now what we paid, but I remember I&#39;ve never been more full or satisfied in my life. Top dining experience.<br><br> A very friendly atmosphere, nice buzz about the place. They&#39;ve got a small outdoor dining area, but it was streaming rain the night I was there.",
