"reviewcomment":"Ristorante Carpaccio is an amazing little spot right on the Grand Canal.  Our concierge recommended this gem on our last night in Venice.  If you are looking for pizza is is not the right spot for you, but if its seafood or seafood pasta you seek, then look no further!!  This place is not the easiest to,see while,walking down the canal it is located in corner behind one of the larger touristy places.<br><br>My wife and I had, had some average experiences our first few meals during our trip to Venice and wanted a real home run for our last night.  When we got there we were sat immediately by the owner Rossario.  We started with a wonderful antipasto Salmon over warm toast with thyme and lemon.  We both went with Seafood Pastas,  my wife had talgliolini  with scallops and zucchini and I had Pappardelle with mixed seafood to which there was plenty of!  Having tried both dishes we both agreed this place nailed it on taste and did over salt or over season it was just right.  The staff was very friendly and attentive.We can&#39;t wait to come back",
