"reviewcomment":"What a little gem this place is. It can be difficult to find this place so plan your route ahead of time. Of course, most places in Venice are hard to find. This great little restaurant is ran by the owners. The wife is the only waitress and the husband is the chef. They were such wonderful hosts and they both chatted and thanked us on our way out.<br><br>This place specializes in seafood and it was all very fresh and cooked beautifully. I really enjoyed the flavor of the cuttlefish cooked in it&#39;s own ink. The only time I&#39;ve ever enjoyed an ink sauce was with this dish. We had several dishes and we were all very full. The highlight of the evening though was after our first and second courses. The homemade tiramisu (family recipe) was outstanding. The best I&#39;ve ever had. The best part of our meal though was the homemade creamy limoncello they make. We ordered a round after the meal and enjoyed it so much they offered us another on the house. We even asked if we could buy a bottle but unfortunately it needs to be freshly made.<br><br>Please check this place out and make reservations beforehand. This place is perfect for a romantic meal in Venice.",
