"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/assets/2/www/img/76df14aad260/default_avatars/business_large_square.png",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"My first real meal in Venice....<br><br>...and it was amazing!<br>Granted, we were here for business and the meal was totally free, so I can&#39;t vouch for prices on things. Basically, there were seven of us and we ordered a set dinner compete with two carafes of perfectly chilled white wine and bottled water.<br><br>First course: A delicious, creamy and amazingly seasoned pasta. I was later told that there was crab in this dish, but alas, I did not taste the crab. All I tasted was 100% deliciousness!<br>Second course: Fish with grilled polenta, olives and roasted cherry tomatoes with a light white wine cream sauce. Super tasty, however I didn&#39;t finish this plate. I&#39;m not sure if it&#39;s because there were a few bones in my fish and I was tired of picking them out, or if it was because I was still full from the pasta.<br>Dessert: We had a huge choice of tiramisu, panna cotta with berry sauce, a fruit cup or a huge hollowed out pineapple, filled with pineapple chunks. We settled on splitting the tiramisu, and definitely don&#39;t regret it.<br>To round out the meal, we ordered coffee (espresso in tiny cups for all you <br>Americans!).<br><br>Again, I&#39;m not sure how much this meal cost but I&#39;m guessing it ain&#39;t cheap. The interior was beautiful and reminded me of old spots in NYC or San Francisco. The waiters were kind and patient, and let us carry out our three hour meal without disruptions.<br><br>Definitely a memorable meal, but I&#39;m not sure if I&#39;d ever go out of my way to eat at this place just because of the potential cost. I&#39;d have to say it&#39;s worth four stars because of 70% food, 30% company. Hurray for places like this!",
