"reviewcomment":"I had really high expectations when I made reservations for lunch at Fiaschetteria Toscana. I had read through the chowhound grapevine that the service can be iffy  but I wanted to give it a shot after the great reviews from Fred Plotkin.<br><br>I entered the restaurant and was greeted really warmly. When I spoke in my basic Italian (thanks Rosetta stone for a great crash course!) and with my dark hair, I think they mistook me for Italian! However, once we were seated and the head waiter burst out in rapid Italian, I obviously was lost! From that point, he removed the menus which were in Italian and handed us the English menus, even though I told him I am comfortable ordering from the Italian menu. The service was snooty from that point on and I wasn&#39;t a happy camper!<br><br>The food is basically the reason for the 3 stars.....I expected a lot more for the price I was paying. For my starter, I ordered a pasta fagioli...it was pretty tasty, all that I wanted in this dish. My husband had seafood pasta and it was ok. The liver and the polenta dish were good but my husband found the liver a bit too salty. For my main, I had a turbot  which was perfectly grilled and deboned, however, it was again too salty. The cheese plate was amazing and they have some of the best gorgonzola I&#39;ve had. The lunch cost us over 100 Euros and maybe they were having a bad day, but some of the dishes were off putting. This was the costliest lunch in Venice and not the best meal I&#39;ve had in this city..",
