"reviewcomment":"On our last night in Venice, Gayle, Erin, Jim and I stayed on Giudecca Island and had dinner here. It was just a short walk from the Hotel Molino Stuckey and well past the overpriced and culturally outlying option of Harry&#39;s Bar.<br><br>Ostaria Ae Botti seemed like more of a locals place, including an interesting display of PDA give-and-take within the Sunday evening &#34;Happy Hour&#34; bunch just behind our table. Our table overlooked the water, and we also did our best to avoid the water that had accumulated on the canopy over our table. <br><br>There might be finer dining out there in great Venice, but this was of those situations when the food, service company, and romantic outdoor venue all came together for a relatively magical moment in time. The next morning, Erin and Jim would be heading to Paris, while Gayle and I would be traveling to the Dolomites. This farewell dinner was our last chance to savor the wonderful week (or so) that we had spent together.",
