"reviewcomment":"After seeing live fish like they&#39;re kissing inside the canals of Venice, there was no way I was going to order seafood for lunch today.<br><br>However, the minute we reached Pointe Rialto, it&#39;s time to eat, and this restaurant was the 1st we come to, and we thought it was PERFECT since we already know what we wanted and the price not so bad - try looking one similar anywhere in price!  But, watching the 2 Japanese tourists to my right, I just pointed our waiter, &#39;I&#39;m having what she&#39;s having!&#39;  I made sure I don&#39;t get calamari!  I had shrimp, and muscles &amp; crabs, but the shrimp was large cut in half, by the time I finished cleaning it, the meat was torn to small pieces, there was nothing LEFT!  (Minus star for no shrimp eaten!  I don&#39;t like eating with my hands!<br><br>Food was delish!  The view a bonus!  The toilette (or W.C. they don&#39;&#39;t call it bathrooms), it lights up once you approached &amp; they&#39;re clean.  The cooks even waved &amp; smiled @ me, while heading to the toilette.  I can&#39;t find a single thing to complain about.  Even their bread, I usually don&#39;t eat their &#39;toast-hard&#39; bread, but this one was soft enough, you&#39;d like to take the rest to nibble while crossing all 400 bridges!  I asked the waiter if he could take a photo of Alan and me, and he said:  &#34;how about a photo of you &amp; ME!&#34;  I said OK, he was so happy &amp; willing to do it, and he was tall, dark &amp; handsome. . . . I could have taken him back home, too!",
